BUILDING THE PROGRAM

   This program was written in C++ and distributed to be built on a 

   Linux system.  To build the program, type 'make' to create the 

   executable called 'prog2'



RUNNING THE PROGRAM

   Type 'prog2' at the command prompt after building the program.



PROGRAM DESCRIPTION

   This program will read dates, then output them on the screen. 



PROGRAM INPUT

   No program input

   

PROGRAM OUTPUT

   All output is written to the screen. 





PROGRAM DESIGN

   This program assigns Date class objects and uses arithmatic operators as well as exceptions





FILE INDEX

   file             function(s)        		description

   --------------   -----------------  		----------------------

   

   main.cpp         main               		calls all other functions



  date.cpp	    Date Constructor		Assigns a date or takes todays date

		    Arthmatic Operators		Allows for basic math with dates

		    Outstream			Allows for output to the screen

  

  date.h	   Date Class 			Initalize the methods 	

		   DateNameSpace Namespace	and variables in the namespace



   makefile              	                builds executable



   README                    	                this file





